article.headline: Maine 67, Colgate 56
article.story: ORONO, Maine -- Mark Socoby scored 21 points and Junior Bernal 17 to lead Maine to a 67-56 victory over Colgate on Monday night. With the score tied at 13, Maine (5-4) scored the next 10 points -- five each by Bernal and Sean McNally. McNally finished with 13. Colgate (2-6) never caught up, although it closed a 35-19 halftime deficit to 47-45 on Joe Hoban's 3-pointer with 7 minutes left. But Socoby scored the next four points and the danger passed as the Black Bears hit their free throws down the stretch. Ben Jonson had 15 points and 12 rebounds for Colgate. Mike Venezia added 12 and Hoban had 8.
